x\in \Bbb R
\dfrac{x}{(x^{2}+x+1)}=\dfrac{1}{4}
\dfrac{x^{3}}{(x^{6}+x^{3}+1)}
x\ne0,
4=\frac{x^2+x+1}x=x+\frac1x+1\implies x+\frac1x=3
\text{Again }\frac{x^3}{x^6+x^3+1}=\frac1{x^3+\frac1{x^3}+1}
\displaystyle a^3+b^3=(a+b)^3-3ab(a+b),
x^3+\frac1{x^3}=\left(x+\frac1x\right)^3-3\cdot x\cdot\frac1x\left(x+\frac1x\right)=\left(x+\frac1x\right)^3-3\left(x+\frac1x\right)
\left(x^m+\frac1{x^m}\right)\left(x^n+\frac1{x^n}\right)=x^{m+n}+\frac1{x^{m+n}}+x^{m-n}+\frac1{x^{m-n}}
\implies x^{m+n}+\frac1{x^{m+n}}=\left(x^m+\frac1{x^m}\right)\left(x^n+\frac1{x^n}\right)-\left(x^{m-n}+\frac1{x^{m-n}}\right)\  \ \ \ (1)
n=1\implies x^{m+1}+\frac1{x^{m+1}}=\left(x^m+\frac1{x^m}\right)\left(x+\frac1x\right)-\left(x^{m-1}+\frac1{x^{m-1}}\right)\  \ \ \ (2)
m=1
(2),
\implies x^2+\frac1{x^2}=\left(x+\frac1x\right)\left(x+\frac1x\right)-\left(x^0+\frac1{x^0}\right)=\left(x+\frac1x\right)^2-2
m=2
(2),
m=2\implies x^3+\frac1{x^3}=\left(x^2+\frac1{x^2}\right)\left(x+\frac1x\right)-\left(x+\frac1x\right)=\left(\left(x+\frac1x\right)^2-2\right)\left(x+\frac1x\right)-\left(x+\frac1x\right)=\left(x+\frac1x\right)^3-3\left(x+\frac1x\right)
